Sep 23 2009 	Amazing view 	The two of us stayed 4 nights for a first-time trip to Chicago and found Hotel 71 to be perfect for what we needed. If you can afford the upgrade, definitely book the Premium/River View level rooms. The riverside views from this hotel are beyond excellent, something you would expect to pay at least $400 a night for and we paid less than $200 through hotels.com. The Premium rooms are on the lower floors, but they are very nicely upgraded, spacious and cozily furnished. Bathrooms have marble, separate tub/shower and dual vanities. Our room was missing the mini-fridge and microwave that the description said would be there, but one phone call to the front desk and both were quickly brought up by the very friendly housekeeping. All of the staff is professional, friendly and non-obtrusive. Our room was spotlessly clean everyday. We also did not notice any noise from the rooms around us. We had zero trouble with the elevators and they came quickly every time. Located at Michigan/Wacker the hotel is two blocks from every train line and many major bus routes. In my opinion, I couldn't have chosen a better hotel, but that said, some travelers may not like a few things. This is not the hotel if you like a lavish restaurant, lobby, and having your hand-held by a concierge. There is an excellent Corner Bakery Cafe next door for breakfast, but only a tiny hotel restaurant. The staff is efficient and mostly invisible (my favorite), but if you want to be greeted a lot . . .you won't be. Perhaps most importantly, you really should request a room away from the elevators, they are older and creaky and you will hear them if your room is close by. Ice is not on every floor, but is easy and generous (extra buckets are stored by the machine). There may be some street noise, but you are in the absolute heart of an enormous city and should expect it. . . bring earplugs.I have traveled quite a bit and think this hotel is actually underrated and nicer than many trendier more expensive places have been, and I've also never had a better location and view for a first trip to a city. We really enjoyed our trip to Chicago and Hotel 71 was a big part of what was good about it.	
