Aug 28 2008 	Very good experience	I have to say, having read some of the reviews about Hotel 71 I was more than a little apprehensive about staying here - I am happy to say I was pleasantly surprised.We booked it through expedia and got a great price for a river view room.Check in was quick and courteous, and the service was attentive and friendly throughout the entire stay. The location is spectacular, right on the river on Whacker Drive, a short walk to the centre of the loop, and the lake. Our very large room on the 31st floor had views from huge windows all the way up the Chicago river.We never had to wait very long for an elevator as some other reviews have mentioned - perhaps I was lucky, but it seemed to me that the hotel has overcome lift congestion by clustering guests on the same floors.The hotel does not have a restaurant, but it's in close proximity to many restaurants and eateries, and for late night dining they have menus at reception for restaurants who will deliver 24hrs. We chose not to have breakfast in the room, but the cafe downstairs next door served and excellent breakfast.Over all it was an enjoyable experience at a very reasonable price. I would definitely stay here again.	
