Aug 12 2008	Good location room fine everything else poor	As the other reviews state, the location is excellent and if you can get a good price then the inconveniences may not matter. However, DO NOT use the phone on any account or you will lose all the savings you have just made. Also, don't expect to sleep in, as housekeeping knock on all the doors between 8 and 8.30 - there is no Do not Disturb sign.The elevators break down frequently and are often too full to get in. You can hear them speeding past your floor without stopping, even though you have called them.Internet access in the business centre is intermittent. Computers did not have adequate virus protection so every time somebody downloaded something they froze up. There is no breakfast room and nowhere like a lounge to sit at all (except a sofa in the lobby). In summer it is not a problem to go to the cafe along the street, but in winter it might be different. Yes, decor is rather sombre, bathtubs strangely flimsy and hot water temperamental.We did not discover there was room service till the last day, as there was nothing to indicate it in the room - no menu or leaflet - In fact, there was not even the usual booklet of hotel services you generally get in hotel rooms. A friend who called us was told the hotel had no record of us - we had prepaid for a week!One day we had clean towels in the morning and they mysteriously disappeared during the day.Phone charges are truly outrageous. The desk clerk told us it cost $27 to pick up the phone for an international call, without actually using any time, and $10 likewise to New York. You could spend hundreds of dollars before finding this out. There is no information about it in the room.We had an excellent trip and would have considered the hotel on balance a fair buy if we had not been royally ripped off on the phone charges at the last minute.	
